            <p>Jewish Theological Seminary Association.<lb/>
                All Communications to be addressed to the Secretary&#44;<lb/>
                No. 237 Broadway&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>JOSEPH BLUMENTHAL&#44; President&#44;<lb/>
                DR. A. FRIEDENWALD&#44; V. President&#44;<lb/>
                NEWMAN COWEN&#44; Treasurer&#44;<lb/>
                JOSEPH E. NEWBURGER&#44; Secretary.</p>					
            <p>New York Dec 23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 1886<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I claim the personal pleasure<lb/> and privilege of acting as the medium of the Board of<lb/> Trustees of this association&#44; to inform you <hi rend="underline">officially</hi> of<lb/> your election to the Presidency of the Seminary&#44; by<lb/> their unanimous vote&#44; at a meeting held on Sunday last<lb/> the 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> inst&#45;&#45;No better evidence of their confidence and<lb/> esteem&#44; than this public announcement that your name<lb/> will be the fullest and best guarantee to the Jews of<lb/> America and of Europe&#44; of the purposes and objects of the<lb/> Seminary&#44; could possibly have been offered or expressed&#45;&#45;<lb/> I take it as a happy omen of the future of that Institution&#44;<lb/> and trust&#44; under God&#39;s guidance and blessing&#44; that it may<lb/> be fruitful of the best results to the cause of Judaism&#44; and<lb/> the perpetuation of its divine and historic principles&#44; and<lb/> mission&#45;&#45;I beg to assure you&#44; that I shall not only<lb/> assist you with my best efforts in every manner possible&#44;<lb/> but that I shall do so with implicit and sincere faith&#44;<lb/> borne of conviction&#44; in the knowledge of your zeal and<lb/> devotion&#44; to the cause which you have so long and so<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>ably championed with your words and your work&#45;&#45;<lb/> I congratulate myself&#44; the Board of Trustees&#44; and<lb/> the Association in securing your valuable services<lb/> and direction for the Seminary&#44; and trust that your<lb/> connection with it may be productive of such<lb/> results as will prove to you a source of genuine<lb/> gratification and satisfaction&#44; to which end be<lb/> again assured I shall second your efforts to the best<lb/> of my humble ability&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Very Respectfully and Sincerely<lb/>
                Your Friend<lb/>
                Joseph Blumenthal<lb/>
                Prest J. T. S. A.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
